# 1. Navigate to your project directory and create a virtual environment.\npython3 -m venv myenv\n\n# 2. Activate it and install dependencies into this virtual environment.\nsource myenv/bin/activate  # On macOS/Linux\n.\myenv\Scripts\activate    # On Windows\n\npip install -r requirements.txt # Assumes you already have a requirements file.\n\n# 3. If not already created, list all required packages with their versions:\npip freeze > requirements.txt\n\n# 4. Create a script to run your Django app.\ntouch run_myapp.sh\nchmod +x run_myapp.sh\n\n# Inside the run_myapp.sh (for macOS/Linux), write:\n#!/bin/bash\nsource myenv/bin/activate\npython manage.py migrate\npython manage.py runserver\n\n# For Windows, you might create a run.bat file instead with:\n@echo off\nmyenv\Scripts\activate\npython manage.py migrate\npython manage.py runserver